HEADWORD: Undertime
<hw>Un"der*time`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Under</ets> +
<er>tide</er>, time. Cf. <er>Undern</er>.]</ety> <def>The under or after
part of the day; undermeal; evening.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He, coming home at <qex>undertime</qex>, there found⟦br⟧
The fairest creature that he ever saw.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

